      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Nothing is known of the Shrewsbury Union Library other than what is given in the 
		collection.  The Constitution, which fills the first five pages, is dated 1824.  It reads, 
		in part:</p>
		
		<blockquote><p>Know ye that we whose names are hereunto subscribed, being desirous to furnish 
		ourselves with useful instruction, have agreed to form ourselves into a Society for the 
		purpose of establishing a Library to be called &amp; known by the name of the Union 
		Library of Shrewsbury...</p></blockquote></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Union Library (Shrewsbury, Vt.) Account Book</emph> consists 
			of a single volume, which includes the Constitution and Bylaws of the Library, along with 
			subscription records, circulation records, and a catalog of books, as follows:</p>
			
			<blockquote>
			<list>
			<item>Constitution, pages 1-5</item>
			<item>Bylaws, pages 12-14</item>
			<item>List of members, pages 15-17</item>
			<item>Minutes of meetings, pages 18-25</item>
			<item>Notes of taxes and other monies paid to the library, by subscriber name, pages 36-92</item>
			<item>Catalog of books, pages 112-128</item></list>
			</blockquote>
      <p>The catalog of books encompasses a wide range of classical and contemporary titles, 
		including <emph render="italic">Pilgrim's Progress</emph>, 
		<emph render="italic">Tristram Shandy</emph>, 
		<emph render="italic">Tales of a Good Woman</emph>, Plutarch's 
		<emph render="italic">Lives</emph>, <emph render="italic">Robinson Crusoe</emph>, Ovid's 
		<emph render="italic">Art of Love</emph>, Paley's <emph render="italic">Philosophy</emph>, 
		Shakespeare's plays, Homer's <emph render="italic">Iliad</emph>, and numerous books of 
		travel, biography and history.</p></scopecontent>
      
